# Code owners: who must approve which changes.
# Syntax and semantics: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# How this file is used here:
# - Submissions are pull requests to `staging` that add files under
#   inbox/<publisher>/... . The entry for /inbox/<publisher>/ names the
#   team that owns that publisher namespace, so their approval is required
#   before a submission can merge — this is what authorizes publishing.
# - Add one /inbox/<publisher>/ line for every publisher declared in
#   publishers.toml, owned by that publisher's team.
# - The entries for publishers.toml, scripts/ and .github/ ensure changes
#   to the authorization config and the automation itself are approved by
#   the index administrators.
#
# Owners must be teams/users with write access, and enforcement requires
# "Require review from Code Owners" in the branch protection rule for
# `staging` (see README setup step 4).

/publishers.toml        @OWNER/index-admins
/scripts/               @OWNER/index-admins
/.github/               @OWNER/index-admins
/inbox/example-publisher/  @OWNER/example-models-team
